---
/**
 * Sectional flag — three rectangles in magenta, lavender, saffron,
 * slightly skewed. Punctuates a heading without screaming "pride flag."
 * Reads as a typographic ornament from a distance, as queer zine signal up close.
 *
 * RTL note: skew direction is mirrored under [dir="rtl"] so the ornament
 * leans the same way relative to reading direction in both languages.
 */
---

<div class="ispc-divider flex items-center gap-1 mb-4" aria-hidden="true">
  <span class="block w-6 h-1.5 bg-magenta"></span>
  <span class="block w-3 h-1.5 bg-lavender"></span>
  <span class="block w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-saffron"></span>
</div>

<style>
  .ispc-divider span {
    transform: skewX(-12deg);
  }
  :global(html[dir="rtl"]) .ispc-divider span {
    transform: skewX(12deg);
  }
</style>
